{
  "name": "Caltrops",
  "type": "consumable",
  "img": "icons/weapons/thrown/bomb-spiked-purple.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span dir=\"ltr\">These four-pronged metal spikes can cause damage to a creature's feet.</span></p><p><span dir=\"ltr\"> You can scatter caltrops in an adjacent space, with a bonus action.</span></p><p><span dir=\"ltr\"> The first creature that moves into that square must succeed at a DC 15 acrobatics check or take 1d4 piercing damage and gain 1 rank of bleed.</span></p><p><span dir=\"ltr\"> A creature who has gained the bleeding condition from caltrops takes a 5-foot penalty to its Speed.</span></p><p><span dir=\"ltr\"> Spending an action to pluck the caltrops free removes the speed penalty, but not the bleeding condition.</span></p><p><span dir=\"ltr\"> Once a creature takes damage from caltrops, enough caltrops are ruined that other creatures moving into the same space are safe.</span></p><p><span dir=\"ltr\"> Deployed caltrops can be salvaged and reused if no creatures took damage from them.</span></p><p></p>",
